ARCHITECTURAL DECISIONS MADE:
- Node.js for game server (not Spring Boot) because physics must run 
  on server and sharing physics.js between client and server requires 
  same language
- Spring Boot used separately as REST API for lobby, player auth, 
  match history, leaderboard (microservices pattern)
- Raw ws over Socket.io to avoid black-box abstractions
- Inputs sent over wire (not state) for anti-cheat